drh added on 2013-06-04 14:48:31:
The order of the output rows in the query below does not honor the
ORDER BY clause.  Specifically, the "y" column is out of order.
CREATE TABLE t1(a INT UNIQUE NOT NULL, b INT NOT NULL);
CREATE INDEX t1ba ON t1(b,a);
CREATE TABLE t2(x INT NOT NULL REFERENCES t1(a), y INT NOT NULL);
CREATE UNIQUE INDEX t2xy ON t2(x,y);
INSERT INTO t1 VALUES(1,1),(3,1);
INSERT INTO t2 VALUES(1,13),(1,15),(3,14),(3,16);

SELECT b, y FROM t1 CROSS JOIN t2 ON x=a ORDER BY b, y;
This problem was apparently introduced by check-in [abcf6a5d054559] and
was first released in version 3.7.15.  The rewritten query planner in the
nextgen-query-plan-exp branch gets the correct answer.  This problem was
discovered while looking for difference plans generated by the nextgen
query planner versus the legacy query planner.
This problem will be fixed when the nextgen query planner is merged to
trunk.  The purpose of this ticket is to record the bug.
